Description: HeroEx, a crowdsourced express delivery service, allows its users to purchase an item via its website and get it delivered within 1 hour.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: HeroEx is "crowdsourced local express delivery". Customers shop at its online storefront at market rate costs, and then get their items delivered in 1 hour or less. HeroEx solves the problem of having to wait days for online purchases to be shipped. It allows you to purchase an item through its website and get it delivered within 1 hour - as long as your item is available locally. HeroEx chose San Francisco as its first test market because of the density of its population and limited geographical area. HeroEx delivers almost anything under 25 lbs in under 1 hour, for just $9-12 -- even cheaper than overnight delivery from FedEx, UPS, and USPS. HeroEx is able to keep its delivery costs low because it has no warehouses, and it crowdsources its Delivery Heroes from the community using a proprietary technology. The company is anticipating that consumers will spend more on a local level once they adopt the concept of affordable local express delivery. For media inquiries, contact: Founder and CEO Marissa Louie marissa@heroex.com (347) 948-HERO

Description: Financial Operations Networks – FON – provides specialized software-as-a-service applications.

Full Description: Financial Operation Networks management team has a collective 105 years’ of operating experience in the accounts payable space. The CEO Phil Binkow and the management team have worked together for a total of 71 years, initially at PayTECH, one of the leading electronic invoice and information processing companies. During that time, PayTECH processed over one hundred million invoices annually, and as you can imagine, spent considerable effort and financial resources answering vendor calls and emails. To eliminate the manual process of answering call after call and email after email, in 1996 the team developed a vendor self-service portal to replace costly manual responses to inquiries. After the sale of PayTECH in 1999 (to Profit Recovery Group [NASDAQ:PRGX]), the team founded Financial Operations Networks, the parent of The Accounts Payable Network (TAPN) and InvoiceInfo. TAPN became the world’s leading resource dedicated to helping AP professionals and their departments become best in class. InvoiceInfo is the payment status portal of choice for leading companies worldwide. Having recently sold The Accounts Payable Network to Diversified Business Communications, the entire focus and mission of FON is to help AP and procurement professionals excel at vendor management through a wide variety of tools and strategies, including its vendor self-service portal, InvoiceInfo

Description: Zephyr Energy Corporation is an innovator of the Wind beam micro energy generator for recharging batteries and electronic devices.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Zephyr Energy Corporation is a Boston-based alternative energy company that is developing a non-rotating wind energy generator.  Zephyr’s wind generator has several competitive advantages including a simple, low cost design, compact form factor, and silent operation. A low cut-in wind speed allows the generator to produce electricity at reduced elevations and in environments unsuitable for wind turbines. Zephyr plans to enter the market with a miniature wind generator product that will meet the low power needs of wireless sensor network (WSN) devices and consumer electronics applications. The industrial WSN market doubled from 2010 to 2012, and is expected to grow 553% by 2017 with over 24 million wireless-enabled sensors installed. A recent industry survey revealed that only 28% of WSN adopters are satisfied with the battery life of their wireless sensor devices. The use of low-power energy harvesting for WSN applications is widespread and increasing annually. Zephyr is seeking funding and/or corporate partners to accelerate the commercialization of its technology. Zephyr’s team is comprised of engineers and business advisors with decades of entrepreneurship and business experience.  Zephyr has partnered with Northeastern University’s Center for Research Innovation and the Gordon Engineering Leadership Program to continue its R&D and commercialization efforts.
Industry Groups: Consumer Electronics, Energy, Hardware, Manufacturing, Sustainability

Our mission is to replace the typical confrontational arguments seen on social media with organized, immersive debates on a wide range of topics. There is currently no organized and engaging way for users to have debates while allowing spectators to watch and decide the outcome. Real Talk provides a platform dedicated to structured live video debates. Full Description: Everyone needs content to drive interest and stay connected with their customers. For some it's their bread and butter, like news organizations, for others it's a way to connect and stay relevant. Some merely need content to drive SEO to their websites. The problem with content is that it requires skills and time to research and write content, and it has to be done on a continuous basis. The job never ends. In addition content is not just text, it requires images, charts, graphs, interactive elements or videos to increase engagement and interest. Creating this is expensive because it takes time, requires specific skills, and has to be performed on an ongoing basis. We have built a  SAAS solution which allow customers to browse a broad range of news articles written by our system. Customers can also create custom content with a few simple inputs in a matter of seconds or minutes. Our content comes ready-to-publish and comes in various formats needed for online publications, such as HTML, plain text, AMP, etc. We also include a variety of media (Images, charts, graphs, video or interactive content), all of which is also created by our systems. Compared to content farms where an article can take days/weeks to be written, we save the customers time and money and allow them to publish much more for much less. Our goal is to provide a constantly growing set of categories and on-demand content, as well as a set of online tools for external content that can be used to augment it.

Description: Eyewire is a game to map 3D structure of neurons to contribute to a scientific discovery.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: EyeWire is a game to map the brain played by over 175,000 people in 150 countries play. One of the world's largest and fastest growing citizen science projects, EyeWire solves a scalability problem in neuroscience: mapping the brain. It takes tens of human hours to decipher, i.e. map, the intricate branches of even a single neuron. Yet there are billions of neurons in a single brain. EyeWire crowdsources this analysis, serving neural reconstructions as 3D puzzles in a game interface. The goals of EyeWire are threefold:  1. Make discoveries relating neural wiring to function;  2. Engage the world in neuroscience and the scientific process;  3. Educate both students and the general public about the brain. Created in 2012. EyeWire's first scientific discovery is published in Nature (May 2014).
